                <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">P(ublius)</supplied> Aelius Lucre<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">tius</supplied> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>vet</abbr><ex>eranus</ex></expan> ex |(centurione) sibi e<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied> <lb n="3"/>Butturae Cypaer<supplied reason="lost">i <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iliae</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>ux</abbr><ex>ori</ex></expan> et Augustae <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iliae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>orum</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Nach Kremer von der Mitte des Sockelgeschosses eine Grabbaus stammend. Z. 1 (Ende): aus Platzgründen eher Lucre[tius] als Lucre[tianus]. (B): Gerstl; Leber; ILLPRON; Kremer: Z. 1: Lucreti[anus]; Gerstl; ILLPRON; Kremer: Z. 3: Cyperi [f(iliae); Leber: Z. 3: Cypaeri[ae].</p>
            </div>
